metadata.name: Seasons #51
metadata.description:
Seasons depicts monolithic mountains and calm seas scattered with unnatural elements.
The color palettes explore the colors of natural landscapes through different times of year.

To ease browser load, the images are paused by default.
Hitting 'p' will toggle a subtle animation.
Hitting 't' will toggle between the day and night palette for the image.
On mobile the resolution is reduced and the image is always paused to ease the load on the device.

Generative images by 0x3739
twitter.com/0x3739
library: twgljs - A Tiny WebGL helper Library
license: CC-BY-NC-SA 4.0
Tested and functioning correctly on Google Chrome version 100.0.4896.88 on Windows desktop and Android mobile device.

The work is rendered in webgl as a fragment shader.
Setting parameters in the javascript portion of the script generates a different fragment shader for each iteration.

Interactions
'-' to zoom in.
'+' to zoom out.
'f' to change the aspect ratio to fullscreen.
'z' to change the aspect ratio to square.
'a' to change the aspect ratio to A4/A3/A2/A1 format.
'w' to change the aspect ratio to 16:9.
'q' to change the aspect ratio to portrait.
's' to save an image of the canvas.
'p' to pause the animation the image.
't' to toggle the time (day/night) in the image.
'b' to toggle the margins on the image.
'm' to toggle the mountains in the image.
'c' to toggle the clouds in the image.
'g' to toggle the grid in the image.
'd' to toggle the dirt speckles in the image.
'n' to toggle the noise in the image.
'j' to toggle the jitter in the image.
'v' to toggle all vintage effects in the image.
'1' to toggle the stars in the image.
'2' to toggle the moons in the image.
'3' to toggle the black squares in the image.
'4' to toggle the white squares in the image.
'5' to toggle the primary color squares in the image.
'6' to toggle the secundary color squares in the image.
'7' to toggle the colour correction in the image.
'8' to toggle the sea in the image.
'h' to increase the quality modifier (maximum is 3).
'l' to decrease the quality modifier (minimum is 1).
The quality modifier is a modifier on the width and height of the canvas.
Changing the modifier can affect the look of the image due to subpixel artifacts.
The modifier can be used to save higher resolution images.
Higher values of the modifier increase memory usage and can cause a browser or webgl instance to crash. 
'arrow_up' to move up in the image.
'arrow_down' to move down in the image.
'arrow_right' to move right in the image.
'arrow_left' to move left in the image.

metadata.name: pang #449
metadata.description:
Within each of us resides an evolutionary history of primal emotions, yet we often spend our lives dulling and controlling these instincts rather than reveling in them. Art is one of the ways we best express those instincts and intuitions ‚Äì accessing and visualizing their visceral qualities, and releasing our deepest emotions in a way we can share.

pang reflects emotions that take control of our impulses ‚Äì anguish, euphoria, obsession. By using crayon-like marks, the artworks convey the catharsis felt while drawing with a childlike abandon. To capture what gives such marks true feeling, the works deliberate the intrinsic movements, pressures, and angles shaped by hands in various moods. These qualities and their frenetic meanderings represent the infinite possibilities of where the crayon could go next ‚Äì if only we could free ourselves from the layers of control we've built.

The contradictions we struggle with are reflected throughout the works:  in the long, methodical, and mathematical path to creation that yields work that looks fast, free and unrehearsed;  through the randomly-informed computer generation of art that feels human;  and by the depiction of long-standing traditional techniques to help display the conceptual range of a young, innovative art movement still establishing its pivotal place in the canon of art. These tensions parallel the work's underlying concept, accentuating the suspicion that a learned fear of emotional expression might just be the source of our own pang. 

Created in p5.js, pang is inspired by the emotional works and processes of later abstract expressionists such as Cy Twombly and Joan Mitchell ‚Äì as well as contemporary artists like Jos√© Parla.

Functionality: 
Press ‚Äòp‚Äô to save as a png. 
Press ‚Äòb‚Äô to render with (or without) a transparent background.
Press 0-9 to render at varying degrees of quality.  0 (lowest quality) to 9 (highest quality, 15000 pixels lengthwise).
Press ‚¨ÜÔ∏è (arrow up) to incrementally increase pixel density.
Press ‚¨áÔ∏è (arrow down) to incrementally decrease pixel density.

__________
TENDER x abstractment
April 2022

metadata.name: Euphonic #1364
metadata.description:
Euphonic is an exploration of the emergent visual properties that arise from placing layers of simple lines atop one another.

In general this effect is called the Moir√© effect. This effect really feels best in the tactile - when you have a printed page and an acetate sheet. This piece attempts to recreate that tactile joy.

This is built in WebGL 2 and so doesn't work in Safari 14 and below. All latest browsers will work as expected.

metadata.name: Arcade Lights #115
metadata.description:
Click anywhere in the image to alter it as you see fit. Play around with it. Have fun!

Arcade Lights is inspired by a bunch of things that bring me joy: Playing video games in my youth, abstract and colorful street graffiti, playful long exposure light photography, wild nights out clubbing, funky retrofuturistic synthwave music.

Press 'p' or 'j' in live mode to save a png or jpg.

In live mode, open the brower's developer tools/devtools/web inspector and go to the console to learn how to produce a static live mode link for the exact image that you've clicked into existence.

Features:
17 vibrant palettes
5 playful ornament styles
3 distinct layouts
2 flow directions
3 draw orders
2 bend directions

I hope Arcade Lights will bring you as much joy as it has me <3

metadata.name: The Three-Body Problem #4
metadata.description:
The Three-Body Problem refers to the difficulty in evaluating an analytical expression for an object under the influence of two massive bodies. This work shows the gravitational vector field from two such bodies. Occasionally, lines will also show curves of equipotential in this field, the centre of mass of the system, the orbital paths traced out. The system is periodic and will loop forever.

Press UP to export one second of frames, and DOWN to save an SVG from the current frame.

metadata.name: Vorticity #75
metadata.description:
Vorticity is a gpu-accelerated flow field. The particles in the flow field orbit around a set of points that move around over time.

Controls: Click and drag to push particles away. Press the space bar to pause the simulation, and again to resume. While paused, you can press "n" to advance the simulation a single step. Press "r" to restart the simulation (if you change the resolution of the screen after the page loads, you will need to restart to update the resolution).
